<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-138-066 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 818 946</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Graphics World  June 1991 v14 n6 p107(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Mac painting venture: Time Arts' Oasis package sports innovations,but still needs to grow. (Software Review) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Steuer, Sharon.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Time Arts' Oasis computer graphics software costs $795 and iscurrently the only Macintosh paint program that enables directaccess to the potential of high-end video boards.andP;  Oasis lackssupport for high-resolution image creation and is not practicalfor creating professional computer images for print.andP;  It may be agood choice if production speed is not a major concern andcomputer painting is used primarily for video applications.andO;Special features include a 'Lightbox' that allows users to seethrough images and view images in a lower layer for hand-tracing,interactive effects and filters, video access and pressuresensitivity.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Time Arts Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   Oasis (Computer graphics software) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     EvaluationGraphics softwarePaint Programs.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>